 of all the alternative models, was recorded\nas 0.9131, but differed slightly (between 0.9138 and 0.9196) for the QMM\ncalibration of the nominal models. The slight differences between these metrics\n(due to computational round off approximations) confirm that when the\ncomponents of basic models are linearly independent, the QMM solution is\nunique.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 23 Feb 2023 20:36:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-27"}
