ework. Finally, we have represented the stiffener, the inner part, and the\nouter part of a B-pillar with G-spline surfaces and solved eigenvalue problems\nusing both Kirchhoff-Love and Reissner-Mindlin shell theories. The results are\ncompared with bilinear quadrilateral meshes and excellent agreement is found\nbetween G-splines and conventional finite elements.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 24 Feb 2023 00:33:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-22"}
