onal viscosities. At higher polymer\nconcentrations, the experimental measurements deviate from the model\npredictions, which is attributed to the onset of intermolecular interactions as\npolymers unravel in the extensional flows. Of practical significance (and\nfundamental interest), elastic instability occurs at a significantly lower Wi\nin uniaxial extensional flow than in either biaxial or planar extensional flow,\nlimiting the utility of this flow type for extensional viscosity measurement.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 24 Feb 2023 02:23:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-02-27"}
